01:26:09.533 --> 01:26:13.957
in NUL, God's really angry with humanity.

01:26:14.578 --> 01:26:15.479
And so it's going to,

01:26:16.279 --> 01:26:19.582
we obviously only succeed to a fairly

01:26:19.764 --> 01:26:22.886
minimal level because most, he says,

01:26:22.926 --> 01:26:25.989
I'm going to make humanity as rare as

01:26:26.850 --> 01:26:28.011
the golden aurifor.

01:26:31.423 --> 01:26:33.364
We don't convince very many people.

01:26:34.904 --> 01:26:39.306
So you have to start with the realization

01:26:39.747 --> 01:26:42.207
that to be successful from God's point of

01:26:42.228 --> 01:26:45.048
view is to be doing what we're doing

01:26:45.908 --> 01:26:46.309
right now.

01:26:47.750 --> 01:26:50.911
To have a committed group of men and

01:26:50.970 --> 01:26:51.850
women who are

01:26:52.440 --> 01:26:53.761
working, who are learning,

01:26:53.822 --> 01:26:56.422
who are loving you and are committed to

01:26:56.462 --> 01:26:57.182
seeing it through,

01:26:57.743 --> 01:27:00.404
from God's point of view, this is success.

01:27:01.466 --> 01:27:06.028
And when you read how the best characters

01:27:06.087 --> 01:27:10.550
in his story struggled through their

01:27:10.590 --> 01:27:10.989
lives,

01:27:11.050 --> 01:27:12.490
and most of them gave up at one

01:27:12.530 --> 01:27:13.211
point or another,

01:27:13.872 --> 01:27:18.073
just finishing the job is success.

01:27:20.680 --> 01:27:21.560
just finishing the job.

01:27:21.581 --> 01:27:24.503
It'll be so rare to finish the job.

01:27:24.524 --> 01:27:25.243
Yeah.

01:27:25.283 --> 01:27:27.305
So, Will, when you first heard this,

01:27:27.445 --> 01:27:29.307
I just think this is such an interesting

01:27:29.948 --> 01:27:33.112
topic to talk about how Yawa has

01:27:33.372 --> 01:27:34.493
intervened all the way through the

01:27:34.533 --> 01:27:34.893
process.

01:27:34.912 --> 01:27:35.573
What are your thoughts?

01:27:36.659 --> 01:27:38.121
Yeah, I mean, I thought that's, again,

01:27:38.180 --> 01:27:38.662
it's, you know,

01:27:38.721 --> 01:27:40.403
it is the ultimate chess move.

01:27:40.443 --> 01:27:42.823
Yawa gives a lot of freedom,

01:27:42.863 --> 01:27:44.345
a lot of free will out there.

01:27:44.706 --> 01:27:46.686
And that's a lot that can go wrong.

01:27:46.726 --> 01:27:48.167
And he's trying to get something very

01:27:48.228 --> 01:27:49.429
specific done.

01:27:51.210 --> 01:27:53.532
So it's just fascinating that it seems

01:27:53.551 --> 01:27:54.931
like that was his solution.

01:27:54.952 --> 01:27:55.932
That's how he deals with it.

01:27:56.554 --> 01:27:58.675
It's like that's his little edge that he

01:27:58.734 --> 01:27:59.114
has.

01:27:59.314 --> 01:27:59.576
You know,

01:27:59.676 --> 01:28:02.157
Yawa has a real sense of fairness and

01:28:02.417 --> 01:28:03.478
gamesmanship.

01:28:03.518 --> 01:28:05.059
But this is what he kind of held

01:28:05.078 --> 01:28:06.119
this back for himself.

01:28:06.539 --> 01:28:07.461
as long as, you know,

01:28:07.501 --> 01:28:09.442
he had the people that he could work

01:28:09.462 --> 01:28:10.904
with of his choosing,

01:28:12.305 --> 01:28:13.085
he can go with that.

01:28:13.164 --> 01:28:15.806
He doesn't need an army of people.

01:28:15.867 --> 01:28:17.087
He needs a handful,

01:28:17.427 --> 01:28:18.529
a few good men and women that he

01:28:18.548 --> 01:28:19.449
can really trust.

01:28:20.029 --> 01:28:21.771
And I think one time you said, yeah,

01:28:21.792 --> 01:28:24.213
I was looking for sort of rough and

01:28:24.253 --> 01:28:25.994
tumble people who are willing to take a

01:28:26.114 --> 01:28:26.574
stand.

01:28:26.815 --> 01:28:27.935
I mean, it's just,

01:28:27.956 --> 01:28:30.078
that's the rough outline of what he's

01:28:30.118 --> 01:28:30.637
looking for.

01:28:30.677 --> 01:28:32.500
Just we, you know, in our, I'm,

01:28:32.640 --> 01:28:33.621
I'm in sales and, uh,

01:28:34.220 --> 01:28:35.461
You know, we call it, you know,

01:28:35.520 --> 01:28:37.322
getting it done or make it happen.

01:28:37.542 --> 01:28:37.721
I mean,

01:28:37.742 --> 01:28:39.742
there are just some people who just make

01:28:39.782 --> 01:28:40.302
things happen.

01:28:40.622 --> 01:28:42.182
You would have been one of those people,

01:28:42.863 --> 01:28:43.203
Yada,

01:28:43.243 --> 01:28:45.024
because you brought companies public.

01:28:45.083 --> 01:28:47.344
So as a CEO with a lot of

01:28:47.404 --> 01:28:48.404
executive function,

01:28:49.345 --> 01:28:50.805
you have a lot of responsibility and,

01:28:51.064 --> 01:28:51.225
you know,

01:28:51.505 --> 01:28:53.365
you obviously were very good at that.

01:28:54.076 --> 01:28:55.176
But I grew up as a salesman.

01:28:55.377 --> 01:28:56.997
That was my career.

01:28:57.158 --> 01:28:58.398
And I was crappy at it.

01:28:58.918 --> 01:29:00.800
And so I had to invent a different

01:29:00.819 --> 01:29:02.400
way to sell because I didn't have the

01:29:02.421 --> 01:29:03.261
personality for it.

01:29:03.980 --> 01:29:10.244
And so what I did essentially was I

01:29:10.524 --> 01:29:14.327
figured out by talking to people what they

01:29:14.787 --> 01:29:15.146
needed.

01:29:15.427 --> 01:29:16.587
Not so much what they wanted,

01:29:17.208 --> 01:29:17.849
what they needed.

01:29:18.569 --> 01:29:21.570
And then I figured out how to provide

01:29:21.770 --> 01:29:23.051
to them what they needed.

01:29:23.752 --> 01:29:25.712
And if you're providing to people what

01:29:25.752 --> 01:29:27.314
they need and you're explaining to them,

01:29:27.814 --> 01:29:30.395
I've surveyed your situation occurred a

01:29:30.456 --> 01:29:31.737
lot about your situation.

01:29:31.777 --> 01:29:32.556
I've thought it through.

01:29:32.617 --> 01:29:33.438
I've examined it.

01:29:33.837 --> 01:29:35.458
And I think this is what you need

01:29:35.578 --> 01:29:36.880
to be successful.

01:29:37.539 --> 01:29:40.042
And I'm here to provide that for you.

01:29:40.122 --> 01:29:40.622
At that point,

01:29:40.641 --> 01:29:41.722
you don't have to sell anything.

01:29:42.594 --> 01:29:43.515
No, no.

01:29:44.896 --> 01:29:46.738
It's very the sales process is very easy

01:29:46.779 --> 01:29:48.621
when you lay it out that way and

01:29:48.640 --> 01:29:50.283
you take away the, you know,

01:29:50.302 --> 01:29:52.604
the salesmanship and the, you know,

01:29:52.985 --> 01:29:55.247
talking constantly and talking fast or

01:29:55.268 --> 01:29:55.609
whatever.

01:29:55.628 --> 01:29:57.930
Your better salespeople are really good

01:29:57.970 --> 01:30:00.293
teachers and communicators and can isolate

01:30:00.474 --> 01:30:02.496
what you need and that they can solve

01:30:02.536 --> 01:30:03.778
that specific need.

01:30:04.582 --> 01:30:06.582
They're very realistic about it.

01:30:06.603 --> 01:30:06.703
Yeah,

01:30:06.722 --> 01:30:09.243
you begin by analyzing what needs to be

01:30:09.564 --> 01:30:12.364
accomplished, and then you provide that.

01:30:12.625 --> 01:30:15.265
And then you demonstrate that when things

01:30:15.305 --> 01:30:16.546
go wrong, and they do.

01:30:16.987 --> 01:30:18.266
And I think this is the thing that

01:30:18.287 --> 01:30:19.587
is so essential to Yahweh.

01:30:19.627 --> 01:30:21.368
He wants us to make mistakes so we

01:30:21.389 --> 01:30:23.088
can learn from them and grow from them.

01:30:23.469 --> 01:30:24.869
He wants us to trip and fall so

01:30:24.890 --> 01:30:26.390
we can get back up and prove that

01:30:26.430 --> 01:30:27.650
we have some stamina and some

01:30:27.930 --> 01:30:28.570
intuitiveness.

01:30:30.252 --> 01:30:32.974
That's the whole thing that changed my

01:30:33.113 --> 01:30:35.574
career as a salesman,

01:30:36.615 --> 01:30:39.837
not only inventing a way to sell such

01:30:39.858 --> 01:30:43.439
that I invested all of my time getting

01:30:43.479 --> 01:30:47.221
to know what the buyers needed to be

01:30:47.301 --> 01:30:50.123
successful and then how I could offer them

01:30:50.264 --> 01:30:52.425
precisely what it was that they needed.

01:30:53.345 --> 01:30:54.365
But the other thing was

01:30:55.463 --> 01:30:57.725
Sometimes the analysis wasn't as good as

01:30:57.784 --> 01:30:58.265
it should have been,

01:30:58.305 --> 01:31:01.286
or sometimes there's other circumstances

01:31:01.365 --> 01:31:03.025
come in that the thought process may have

01:31:03.046 --> 01:31:05.146
been outstanding, but it just didn't work.

01:31:06.386 --> 01:31:09.368
And very early in the process,

01:31:10.127 --> 01:31:11.429
every time there was a problem,

01:31:12.769 --> 01:31:13.668
I fixed the problem.

01:31:14.509 --> 01:31:15.529
If a product didn't sell,

01:31:15.670 --> 01:31:16.329
I bought it back.

01:31:18.707 --> 01:31:23.412
I became the guarantor for the buyers that

01:31:23.453 --> 01:31:24.113
I represented.

01:31:24.274 --> 01:31:26.015
The word got out that a buyer could

01:31:26.036 --> 01:31:27.277
not get themselves into trouble.

01:31:27.296 --> 01:31:29.439
They could not make a bad purchase if

01:31:29.460 --> 01:31:32.523
they trusted me on a promotion.

01:31:32.963 --> 01:31:34.845
That if it failed, I'd buy it back.

01:31:35.386 --> 01:31:36.287
And you might say, you know,

01:31:36.327 --> 01:31:37.886
how do you do that if you're getting

01:31:37.947 --> 01:31:39.247
started as a salesman?

01:31:39.688 --> 01:31:40.108
I'll tell you what,

01:31:40.148 --> 01:31:41.368
it was really tough initially.

01:31:41.448 --> 01:31:43.289
But when you get a reputation for doing

01:31:43.310 --> 01:31:43.449
that,

01:31:43.609 --> 01:31:45.511
everybody wants to do business with you.

01:31:45.990 --> 01:31:47.591
And it makes so daggone much money on

01:31:47.631 --> 01:31:48.131
commission.

01:31:48.432 --> 01:31:49.632
Everybody wanted to do business with you

01:31:49.653 --> 01:31:52.373
becomes really easy to buy stuff back.

01:31:52.474 --> 01:31:53.774
And when you buy it back,

01:31:53.854 --> 01:31:56.315
you you generate more business than you

01:31:56.336 --> 01:31:57.157
could ever imagine.

01:31:57.176 --> 01:31:57.577
Right.

01:31:57.957 --> 01:31:58.957
Yeah, that was the brilliance.

01:31:58.978 --> 01:32:00.759
That was the brilliance of Value America.

01:32:01.019 --> 01:32:02.119
Craig, you essentially,

01:32:02.800 --> 01:32:04.962
you made them an offer they couldn't

01:32:05.021 --> 01:32:06.402
refuse if they had a brain.

01:32:07.122 --> 01:32:07.422
Yes.

01:32:08.344 --> 01:32:08.583
Yeah,

01:32:08.944 --> 01:32:11.045
it was a much better mousetrap than Amazon

01:32:11.085 --> 01:32:12.947
even is today.

01:32:14.006 --> 01:32:17.349
But, you know, things happen,

01:32:17.949 --> 01:32:18.909
and the way things happen,

01:32:18.949 --> 01:32:21.332
it led to this opportunity.

01:32:22.283 --> 01:32:23.543
You know, one last thing, Craig,

01:32:23.564 --> 01:32:27.005
that's really remarkable to me,

01:32:27.104 --> 01:32:29.386
it's how much Yahweh trusts us.

01:32:29.506 --> 01:32:30.686
It's Amunah,

01:32:31.167 --> 01:32:34.087
and so Yahweh asks us to trust Him.

01:32:34.127 --> 01:32:35.948
He really wants that,

01:32:36.228 --> 01:32:38.149
but He's willing to demonstrate to you,

01:32:38.208 --> 01:32:40.349
or at least to this group of people,

01:32:40.389 --> 01:32:41.510
this A-team,

01:32:41.949 --> 01:32:43.850
or whatever we want to call them,

01:32:44.331 --> 01:32:46.430
the A-team, you know,

01:32:46.490 --> 01:32:48.492
and He set this up well.

01:32:50.051 --> 01:32:50.470
He does,

01:32:50.610 --> 01:32:52.792
and there's all sorts of times where I

01:32:52.813 --> 01:32:52.912
say,

01:32:53.993 --> 01:32:56.275
are you sure you're managing this

01:32:56.336 --> 01:32:56.815
