01:32:57.195 --> 01:32:59.997
I mean, I know me, and, you know,

01:33:00.018 --> 01:33:02.119
I'm not sure I would roll the dice

01:33:02.140 --> 01:33:02.520
with me.

01:33:02.539 --> 01:33:03.421
I mean,

01:33:03.440 --> 01:33:04.560
I'm not going to give up on you.

01:33:06.842 --> 01:33:09.685
I'm happy to have the job and everything,

01:33:09.744 --> 01:33:11.605
but certainly you should have been able to

01:33:11.627 --> 01:33:12.386
do better than me.

01:33:13.608 --> 01:33:15.069
And, you know, then he says, no,

01:33:15.109 --> 01:33:17.490
you're pretty much what I expected, and,

01:33:17.610 --> 01:33:18.692
you know, you're doing great.

01:33:19.434 --> 01:33:20.454
pretty good for a young man.

01:33:22.034 --> 01:33:24.396
That's just his approach.

01:33:26.618 --> 01:33:28.059
He's not looking for perfection.

01:33:28.878 --> 01:33:31.461
As soon as that weight is removed from

01:33:31.501 --> 01:33:31.640
you,

01:33:31.661 --> 01:33:33.301
that he is not looking for perfection,

01:33:34.082 --> 01:33:36.262
he wants us to make mistakes so we

01:33:36.283 --> 01:33:36.923
can correct them.

01:33:37.724 --> 01:33:40.546
I tell that to my favorite fact checker

01:33:40.565 --> 01:33:43.287
