01:34:01.927 --> 01:34:03.408
ago,

01:34:03.429 --> 01:34:04.949
knowing that we would find it at the

01:34:04.989 --> 01:34:06.550
right time that we so we could use

01:34:06.609 --> 01:34:06.690
it.

01:34:06.751 --> 01:34:08.350
And we would laugh along with them and

01:34:08.371 --> 01:34:10.532
say, I remember when two days ago,

01:34:10.572 --> 01:34:12.353
Rich walked into my study and I had

01:34:12.412 --> 01:34:13.234
just translated.

01:34:13.274 --> 01:34:13.774
I said, Richard,

01:34:13.793 --> 01:34:15.255
just not going to believe this will just

01:34:15.274 --> 01:34:15.854
blow your mind.

01:34:16.380 --> 01:34:17.520
This is so funny.

01:34:18.400 --> 01:34:19.761
And that happens all the time.

01:34:20.121 --> 01:34:22.181
So that takes the burden off.

01:34:22.221 --> 01:34:23.962
And then when you realize, finally,

01:34:24.002 --> 01:34:25.282
what Doe did on Himatsa,

01:34:25.301 --> 01:34:26.983
where he took our guilt and deposited it

01:34:27.002 --> 01:34:27.422
